INSERT INTO test2_content VALUES("51","2013-01-22 17:14:00","2013-01-22 19:13:56","","1","1","post","lg-optimus-g-pro-official-for-japan-5-inch-1080p-lcd-1-7ghz","","LG Optimus G Pro official for Japan: 5-inch 1080p LCD, 1.7GHz S4 Pro and Jelly Bean","2","","&lt;p&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.engadget.com/2013/01/21/lg-optimus-g-pro-official-ntt-docomo/&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;LG Optimus G Pro official 5inch 1080p LCD, 17GHz Snapdragon S4 Pro and an NTT DoCoMo launch&quot; data-src-height=&quot;450&quot; data-src-width=&quot;619&quot; src=&quot;{SITE_URL}userfiles/media/downloaded/ef6d957aed68e5374758ceb43ddab45clg-optimus-g-pro-1358828027.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; Remember how the &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.engadget.com/2013/01/18/lg-optimus-g-pro-spec-leak/&quot;&gt;LG Optimus G Pro&lt;/a&gt; saw its biggest leak in Japan? We might just know why. Local carrier NTT DoCoMo has confirmed the new flagship\'s existence as part of a spring device lineup, and it\'s everything that was rumored just days ago. LG is adding to the rapidly burgeoning crowd of 5-inch, 1080p phones while freshening the formula we\'d seen in the regular &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.engadget.com/2012/10/19/lg-optimus-g-review-a-quad-core-powerhouse-with-nexus-aspiratio/&quot;&gt;Optimus G&lt;/a&gt;: there\'s now a quicker, 1.7GHz &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.engadget.com/tag/SnapdragonS4Pro/&quot;&gt;Snapdragon S4 Pro&lt;/a&gt; chip, a heftier 3,000mAh battery and Jelly Bean (albeit &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.engadget.com/2012/06/28/android-4-1-jelly-bean-review-a-look-at-whats-changed-in-googl/&quot;&gt;Android 4.1&lt;/a&gt;, not 4.2) out of the box. Other elements are familiar carryovers, such as the 2GB of RAM, 13-megapixel camera, 32GB of built-in storage, a microSDXC slot and LTE. Japanese buyers will have to wait until early April to pick up an Optimus G Pro for themselves; as LG hasn\'t confirmed the phone separately, other countries\' launches are still up in the air.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Filed under: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.engadget.com/category/cellphones/&quot; rel=&quot;tag&quot;&gt;Cellphones&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.engadget.com/category/mobile/&quot; rel=&quot;tag&quot;&gt;Mobile&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.engadget.com/category/lg/&quot; rel=&quot;tag&quot;&gt;LG&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.engadget.com/2013/01/21/lg-optimus-g-pro-official-ntt-docomo/#comments&quot;&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Source:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;http://translate.google.com/translate?sl=ja","y","n","n","n","n","post","","http://www.engadget.com/2013/01/21/lg-optimus-g-pro-official-ntt-docomo/","","","","","eb3701e0fg3ocgiq0u98o7nfd3"); /* MW_TABLE_SEP */
INSERT INTO test2_content VALUES("52","2013-01-22 17:14:04","2013-01-22 19:14:00","","1","1","post","watch-men-cringe-and-cry-in-pain-as-they-go-through-a-simula","","Watch Men Cringe and Cry in Pain As They Go Through a Simulation of Giving Birth","2","","&lt;div&gt; &lt;!-- div style=&quot;background-color: #B3B3B3; width: 190px; padding: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;a title=&quot;Click here to read Watch Men Cringe and Cry in Pain As They Go Through a Simulation of Giving Birth&quot; href=&quot;http://gizmodo.com/pregnancy/&quot; style=&quot;background-color:#888888; color:#FFFFFF; font-size:12px;text-align:right; display:block; height:14px; padding:1px 2px; text-decoration:none; text-transform:uppercase; width:156px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: white;&quot; class=&quot;hash&quot;&gt;#&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: white;&quot;&gt;pregnancy&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div --&gt; &lt;div&gt;&lt;a title=&quot;Click here to read Watch Men Cringe and Cry in Pain As They Go Through a Simulation of Giving Birth&quot; href=&quot;http://gizmodo.com/5977868/watch-men-cringe-and-cry-for-help-as-they-go-through-a-labor-simulation&quot;&gt; &lt;img height=&quot;360&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; title=&quot;Click here to read Watch Men Cringe and Cry in Pain As They Go Through a Simulation of Giving Birth&quot; alt=&quot;Click here to read Watch Men Cringe and Cry in Pain As They Go Through a Simulation of Giving Birth&quot; src=&quot;{SITE_URL}userfiles/media/downloaded/416b61f8a686f454ada709e17c4b6dc1original.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;!-- videoId: ZlsPXpR2ORU --&gt;&lt;!-- /videoId: ZlsPXpR2ORU --&gt; Women have the ultimate trump card when it comes to dealing with pain: they give birth. And since men have no idea what giving birth even feels like, we really don\'t know how painful it really is. Maybe it\'s all a big conspiracy (kidding!). Maybe it\'s not &lt;em&gt;that&lt;/em&gt; bad (of course it is!). Well, two men attached themselves to a machine that simulates labor pains and um, it ain\'t pretty. It looks torturously gruesome. Thank you women everywhere. Thank you. &lt;a href=&quot;http://gizmodo.com/5977868/watch-men-cringe-and-cry-for-help-as-they-go-through-a-labor-simulation&quot; title=&quot;Click here to read more about Watch Men Cringe and Cry in Pain As They Go Through a Simulation of Giving Birth&quot;&gt;More","y","n","n","n","n","post","","http://feeds.gawker.com/~r/gizmodo/full/~3/FXdCwOlOI_Y/watch-men-cringe-and-cry-for-help-as-they-go-through-a-labor-simulation","","","","","eb3701e0fg3ocgiq0u98o7nfd3"); /* MW_TABLE_SEP */
INSERT INTO test2_content VALUES("53","2013-01-22 17:14:08","2013-01-22 19:14:04","","1","1","post","the-east-trailer-anarchists-and-eco-terrorism-video","","\'The East\' Trailer: Anarchists and Eco-Terrorism (Video)","2","","&lt;img src=&quot;{SITE_URL}userfiles/media/downloaded/162e68542f59396f80b7b1e0854a638aTheEast.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;The thriller, which made its debut at Sundance, is directed by Zal Batmanglij and produced by Ridley Scott.&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/east-trailer-anarchists-eco-terrorism-414204&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;read more&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;img width=&quot;1&quot; height=&quot;1&quot; src=&quot;http://rss.feedsportal.com/c/34793/f/641578/s/27c2d646/mf.gif&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;table border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td valign=&quot;middle&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://share.feedsportal.com/viral/sendEmail.cfm?lang=en","y","n","n","n","n","post","","http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/thr/news/~3/hDFWK0NyPIU/story01.htm","","","","","eb3701e0fg3ocgiq0u98o7nfd3"); /* MW_TABLE_SEP */
INSERT INTO test2_content VALUES("54","2013-01-22 17:14:12","2013-01-22 19:14:08","","1","1","post","blackfish-sundance-review","","Blackfish: Sundance Review","2","","&lt;img src=&quot;{SITE_URL}userfiles/media/downloaded/3fd71e9369840a54eab174fba9e57aedBlackfish.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;This stirring documentary tells the real-life version of tragedies involving killer whales in captivity, like the one depicted in awards season contender &quot;Rust and Bone.&quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/blackfish-sundance-review-414203&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;read more&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;img width=&quot;1&quot; height=&quot;1&quot; src=&quot;http://rss.feedsportal.com/c/34793/f/641578/s/27c296dc/mf.gif&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;table border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td valign=&quot;middle&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://share.feedsportal.com/viral/sendEmail.cfm?lang=en","y","n","n","n","n","post","","http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/thr/news/~3/vpP41z7YAq0/story01.htm","","","","","eb3701e0fg3ocgiq0u98o7nfd3"); /* MW_TABLE_SEP */
INSERT INTO test2_content VALUES("55","2013-01-22 17:14:16","2013-01-22 19:14:12","","1","1","post","cuba-s-undersea-fiber-cable-potentially-sees-consumer-intern","","Cuba\'s undersea fiber cable potentially sees consumer internet use for first time","2","","&lt;p&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.engadget.com/2013/01/21/cuba-undersea-fiber-cable-internet/&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;Cuba\'s undersea fiber cable potentially sees consumer internet use for first time&quot; data-src-height=&quot;340&quot; data-src-width=&quot;620&quot; src=&quot;{SITE_URL}userfiles/media/downloaded/33a8d115c4d46e86d357529363d83d83cuba.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; An underwater fiber cable linking Cuba and Venezuela has given the island a hard connection to the internet since 2011, but reports have said that only government bodies from both countries have used the line. According to internet and network analysis firm &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.engadget.com/2012/11/01/time-lapse-hurricane-sandy-internet-outages/&quot;&gt;Renesys&lt;/a&gt;, the cable lit up with activity last week with data flowing through it between &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.engadget.com/tag/Telefonica/&quot;&gt;Telefonica&lt;/a&gt; and the nation\'s state telecom company, Empresa de Telecomunicaciones de Cuba S.A. (ETECSA). Presumably, this could signal use by the average joe. Traceroutes into Cuba through the new Telefonica path show markedly lower latencies than the Caribbean country\'s existing &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.engadget.com/tag/SatelliteInternet/&quot;&gt;satellite-reliant connections&lt;/a&gt;, hinting that the cable has been flipped on -- at least in one direction. It appears that the ETECSA is using the line for inbound data while leaning on satellites for outbound traffic.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; Despite the clues, a &lt;em&gt;GlobalPost&lt;/em&gt; correspondent in Cuba says there has been no perceptible improvement in internet speeds as of yet. Castro and Co. may not have said a peep about the development, but the new Telefonica path surfaced the very same day Cuba nixed the requirement of exit visas for citizens to travel outside its borders. Hit the source link for network stats and the nitty gritty details.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; [Image credit: Phil Guest, &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.flickr.com/photos/philip-rosie/5439094210/&quot;&gt;Flickr&lt;/a&gt;]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Filed under: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.engadget.com/category/internet/&quot; rel=&quot;tag&quot;&gt;Internet&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.engadget.com/2013/01/21/cuba-undersea-fiber-cable-internet/#comments&quot;&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Via:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://www.ubergizmo.com/2013/01/cuba-activates-under-sea-fiber-optic-cable-for-incoming-traffic-only/&quot;&gt;Ubergizmo&lt;/a&gt;&lt;!--//--&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Source:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://www.renesys.com/blog/2013/01/cuban-mystery-cable-activated.shtml&quot;&gt;Renesys&lt;/a&gt;&lt;!--//--&gt;&lt;/p&gt;","y","n","n","n","n","post","","http://www.engadget.com/2013/01/21/cuba-undersea-fiber-cable-internet/","","","","","eb3701e0fg3ocgiq0u98o7nfd3"); /* MW_TABLE_SEP */
